--- body ---
## Context

`test_golden_values.py::TestGoldenValues::test_method_matches_golden` fails for all 10 methods with:

```
AssertionError: S1_MMD: shape mismatch — golden (108, 5), fresh (96, 5)
```

The golden CSVs in `tests/fixtures/smoke/golden/` were generated when the smoke fixture output had
108 rows (year×window combinations). The current corpus produces 96 rows. This is data drift, not a
code regression. 15 golden files exist; G9/C2ST have no golden files (test auto-skips them).

## Relevant files

- `tests/fixtures/smoke/golden/tab_div_*.csv` — 15 stale golden CSV files
- `tests/test_golden_values.py` — compares fresh output shape AND values (atol=1e-6); `@pytest.mark.slow`
- `scripts/compute_divergence.py` — the regeneration script

## Actions

`make regression-update` regenerates `golden_hashes.json` (figure hashes), NOT the divergence golden
CSVs — do not use it. Run manually:

```bash
SMOKE="$(pwd)/tests/fixtures/smoke"
GOLDEN="${SMOKE}/golden"
for method in \
  S1_MMD S2_energy S3_sliced_wasserstein S4_frechet \
  L1 L2 L3 \
  G1_pagerank G2_spectral G3_coupling_age G4_cross_tradition \
  G5_pref_attachment G6_entropy G7_disruption G8_betweenness; do
  PYTHONHASHSEED=0 SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH=0 CLIMATE_FINANCE_DATA="${SMOKE}" \
    uv run python scripts/compute_divergence.py \
      --method "${method}" \
      --output "${GOLDEN}/tab_div_${method}.csv"
done
git add tests/fixtures/smoke/golden/tab_div_*.csv
git commit -m "chore: regenerate golden values (102-work smoke fixture)"
```

**Machine caveat:** S1–S4 auto-detect CUDA. Golden files must be regenerated on the same
backend (CPU or GPU) where tests will run. On padme (GPU), torch is used — regenerate there.

**G9/C2ST**: no golden files exist for these — tests auto-skip. Do not create them.

**S4_frechet**: after 0118 lands (get_min_papers smoke-mode fix), smoke mode returns min_papers=5
so results will be non-empty. The regenerated S4 golden will have actual rows.

## Test

```bash
uv run pytest tests/test_golden_values.py -v
```

## Exit criteria

- [ ] `pytest tests/test_golden_values.py` passes for all methods (10 with golden files pass, 5 skip)
- [ ] Golden CSVs committed with message "chore: regenerate golden values (102-work smoke fixture)"

